@node "introduction" "AmiGenerator - Introduction"

 This is a Sega MegaDrive/Genesis emulator developed by James Ponder.

@endnode

@node "requirements" "AmiGenerator - Requirements"

 Hardware:

  * Amiga with a PowerPC board
  * 8 MB of RAM
  * OS 3.0+

 Software:

  * CGFX v3 or later for CGFX support
  * WarpUP v4.0
  * lowlevel.library for CD32 pad support

@endnode

@node "features" "AmiGenerator - Features"

 This is what's being emulated:

 CPU
  * 68000 @ 8MHz.
  * Z80 @ 4MHz.

 Video
  * Linebased emulation (optional framebased one for higher speed).
  * Highlight/Shadow effects.
  * Supports palette changes in mid screen.
  * Interlaced mode support.
  * ...

 Audio
  * Linebased emulation.
  * PSG (SN76489).
  * FM (YM2612).

@endnode

@node "installation" "AmiGenerator - Installation"

 Just copy it to any place on your HD.

@endnode

@node "usage" "AmiGenerator - Usage"

 There are currently two versions of AmiGenerator included in this archieve.

 The "normal" one called just AmiGenerator.exe is based upon the portable
 console interface which add a lot of features and always uses 15/16bit display
 to support all Genesis/MegaDrive features.

 Then there is the T-version (AmiGeneratorT.exe) which is an atempt to make
 AmiGenerator as fast as possible. It uses a lower sound frequency, it only
 support 8bit display, and it uses all tricks in the book to make the AmigaOS
 code as fast as possible.

 No matter which one you choose, just type the filename to get a list of
 supported options.

 * AmiGenerator options:

  SIMPLE/S    : simple VDP emulation.
  FRAMESKIP/N : frameskip 1-10 (def: 3).
  NOSOUND/S   : disable Z80, YM2612 and SN76489 emulation.
  NOZ80/S     : disable Z80 emulation.
  NOFM/S      : disable YM2612 emulation.
  NOPSG/S     : disable SN76489 emulation.
  LACE/K      : select de-interlace mode (bob, weave, weave-filter).
  LATENCY/N   : number of video fields worth of sound to try to keep buffered.
  FRAGMENTS/N : number of video fields worth of sound to allow buffered.
  FREQ/N      : sound frequency (def: 22050, 11025 for T version).
  JOYPAD/S    : CD32 joypad (+ keyboard for 2nd player) (def: keyboard only).
  REQ/S       : use screenmode requester (def: CGFX BestModeID/PAL Lores).

  NOTE: The LACE setting only makes a difference in the console version.


  Settings/Functions, T-version ONLY:

   F5        - Complex VDP (slow and accurate)
   F6        - Simple VDP (fast but not very accurate)
   1,2,3...0 - Frameskip 1-10
   HELP      - Saves the current screen as a PCX file


  Keyboard

   ESC        - Quit
   A          - A Button
   S          - B Button
   D          - C Button
   Enter      - Start
   Arrow keys - Left, Right, Up, Down


  CD32 pad support uses:

   Red button    - A Button
   Blue button   - B Button
   Yellow button - C Button
   Play button   - Start
   Left, Right   - Left, Right
   Up, Down      - Up, Down

@endnode

